# Technical Specification
## Multi-Station Packaging Line — Mechanical Installation

## 1. Purpose & Scope
Define the functional, mechanical, and electrical requirements for
installing and commissioning a multi-station packaging line: mechanical
installation/alignment through to sequenced, interlocked operation —
representative of packaging/production lines in food processing plants.

## 2. Functional Block Diagram
```mermaid
flowchart LR
    IN[Incoming Product] --> S1[Station 1: Load]
    S1 --> S2[Station 2: Transfer/Pack]
    S2 --> S3[Station 3: Seal]
    S3 --> OUT[Outgoing Packaged Product]
    CTRL[PLC / Sequence Controller] -->|Step Commands| S1
    CTRL -->|Step Commands| S2
    CTRL -->|Step Commands| S3
    S1 -->|Sensor Feedback| CTRL
    S2 -->|Sensor Feedback| CTRL
    S3 -->|Sensor Feedback| CTRL
    ESTOP[E-Stop / Safety Circuit] -->|Hardwired| S1
    ESTOP -->|Hardwired| S2
    ESTOP -->|Hardwired| S3
```

## 3. Electrical Schematic — Control Circuit Overview
```
Control Voltage (24VDC):
  PLC DO (Station Step Cmd)  -----> Station Actuator (pneumatic/electric)
  Station Sensor (Present)   -----> PLC DI (Step confirmation)
  Station Sensor (Fault)     -----> PLC DI (Fault detection)
  E-Stop chain               -----> Hardwired to all station actuators
                                     (safety interlock, independent of PLC)

Pneumatic supply (if applicable):
  Main air supply --> [Filter/Regulator/Lubricator] --> Station solenoid
  valves --> Station cylinders/actuators
```

### I/O List (per station, representative)
| Signal | Type | From | To | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Step Command | Digital Out | PLC | Station actuator | Advances sequence step |
| Part Present Sensor | Digital In | Station | PLC | Confirms step completion |
| Fault Sensor | Digital In | Station | PLC | Detects jam/fault condition |
| E-Stop | Hardwired | Safety circuit | All stations | Safety interlock |

## 4. Mechanical Schematic — Station Layout
```
[Infeed] --> [Station 1: Load] --> [Station 2: Pack] --> [Station 3: Seal] --> [Outfeed]

Foundation: individual station base frames, leveled and anchored
Alignment: transfer points between stations aligned to product handoff
tolerance (per `mechanical-installation-procedure.md`)
Guarding: perimeter guarding with interlocked access points at each station
```

## 5. System Constants & Parameters
| Parameter | Value/Range | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Control voltage | 24VDC | PLC/sensor/actuator standard |
| Pneumatic supply pressure | 80-100 psi (typical) | Per actuator manufacturer spec |
| Station cycle time | Application-dependent | Balanced across stations to avoid bottlenecks |
| Sensor response time | <20 ms typical | Ensures reliable step confirmation |
| E-Stop response | Hardwired, <10 ms | Independent of PLC scan cycle |
| Alignment tolerance (transfer points) | Per equipment spec, typically <1-2 mm | Prevents jams at handoff |

## 6. Alignment with Industry Expectations (JBS & similar plants)
- **Blueprint-driven installation**: layout and I/O documented before
  installation, matching "read blueprints, diagrams and schematic drawings
  to determine work procedures"
- **Staged commissioning**: mechanical verification before electrical
  energization, reducing risk of equipment damage
- **Safety-first interlocks**: E-stop hardwired independently across all
  stations, appropriate for food-processing environments with moving
  machinery
- **Sequenced fault handling**: GRAFCET-based logic prevents cascading
  faults across stations, minimizing downtime and product loss

